<%- include('../layouts/header', { title: title || 'Documentation' }) %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-electric-blue py-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8 fadeIn">Documentation: Bot Token Setup</h1>

        <div class="bg-blue-800/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How to Create Your Discord Bot and Get a Token</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Follow these steps to create a bot and retrieve its token from the Discord Developer Portal.</p>

            <ol class="space-y-4 text-gray-300">
                <li>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Step 1: Create a Discord Application</h3>
                    <p>1. Visit the <a href="https://discord.com/developers/applications" class="text-electric-blue hover:text-blue-600" target="_blank">Discord Developer Portal</a>.</p>
                    <p>2. Click on the "New Application" button at the top right corner.</p>
                    <p>3. Enter a name for your application (this will be the bot's name) and click "Create".</p>
                    <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/jSkKDHrM/CREATE.png" alt="Create Application" class="w-full rounded-lg mt-4">
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Step 2: Create a Bot</h3>
                    <p>1. In the sidebar, go to the "Bot" tab under the application settings.</p>
                    <p>2. Click on the "Add Bot" button and confirm by clicking "Yes, do it!".</p>
                    <p>3. Customize your bot's profile, including name and icon.</p>
                    <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/wTg9ZxVQ/NAME.png" alt="Create Bot" class="w-full rounded-lg mt-4">
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Step 3: Get Your Bot Token</h3>
                    <p>1. On the Bot settings page, you'll see the "Token" section.</p>
                    <p>2. Click on the "Copy" button to copy your bot's token.</p>
                    <p>**Important**: Keep your bot token secure! Do not share it publicly or expose it in your code.</p>
                    <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/JhD8ZsrM/TOKEN.png" alt="Get Token" class="w-full rounded-lg mt-4">
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Step 4: Set Up Bot Permissions</h3>
                    <p>1. In the "OAuth2" tab, under "OAuth2 URL Generator", select the necessary bot permissions (e.g., "Send Messages", "Manage Messages", etc.).</p>
                    <p>2. Use the generated URL to invite your bot to a server.</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1401361799818907659/1403902868884422666/image.png?ex=68993def&is=6897ec6f&hm=f86ec6fadb0b5219a8883609487b8c5495af734f1446cb9bbaf1228056749e89&" alt="Bot Permissions" class="w-full rounded-lg mt-4">
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

